 syslog Daemon
                                                                                                                         
 A program to receive, process, and send syslog messages.  
    System processes and critical applications log the events and states you're interested in (based on the syslog.conf). 
    It can send syslog remotely to a centralized server or write it to a local file. 

Common examples include rsyslogd and syslog-ng. 

    found in /etc
================================================================

    syslog Protocol


A transport protocol specifying how logs can be sent over a network and a data format definition for syslog messages. It’s officially defined in RFC-5424. 

The standard ports are 514 for plain text logs and 6514 for encrypted logs.

Log messages or events in the syslog format, which includes a header with several standard fields.

===============================================================

    
